===Etymology===
{{wikipedia|dab=lexicon (disambiguation)|lexicon}}
{{root|en|ine-pro|*leǵ-}}
Through {{bor|en|frm|-}} or directly from {{bor|en|NL.|lexicon}}, from {{der|en|gkm|λεξικόν||a lexicon, a dictionary}}, [[ellipsis]] from {{der|en|grc||λεξικὸν βιβλίον|lit=a book of words}}, from {{m|grc|λεξικός||of words}}, from {{m|grc|λέξις||a saying, speech, word}}, from {{m|grc|λέγειν|λέγω|to speak}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*leǵ-||to gather, collect}}.

Attested at least since 1583 (in {{w|William Fulke}}'s ''A Defense of the Sincere and True Translations of the Holy Scriptures into the English tongue'') in the sense 'a dictionary of a classical language'.

